cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use feral in academic work or published benchmarks, please cite it."
title: "feral: Rigorous quality benchmarking for local LLMs"
abstract: >-
  feral is a Python framework for deterministic, reproducible benchmarking of
  locally hosted large language models. It captures full run provenance (model
  SHA, suite SHA, quantization, KV cache type, generation parameters), supports
  LLM-as-judge scoring with debiasing and calibration, and produces paired
  statistical comparisons (bootstrap confidence intervals, Cohen's d effect
  sizes) across models and quantization levels.
type: software
